# Language Configuration File
# 
# This file defines the target languages for batch translation and the translation engine to use.
# Each line should contain a language code and name separated by a delimiter.
#
# Supported delimiters: colon (:), comma (,), or equals sign (=)
# Format: <language-code><delimiter><language-name>
#
# Examples:
#   en:English
#   de,German
#   fr=French
#
# Lines starting with # are treated as comments and ignored.
# Blank lines are also ignored.
#
# To use this file:
# 1. Copy this file to 'languages.conf' in your working directory
# 2. Customize the language list and engine as needed
# 3. Run the translation tool (it will automatically detect the file)
#
# Alternative configuration methods:
# - Use --config or -c flag: translate --config /path/to/languages.conf
# - Set environment variable: TRANSLATE_CONFIG_PATH=/path/to/languages.conf
#
# Priority: CLI option > Environment variable > Default location (./languages.conf)

# Note: This tool uses Google Translate as the translation engine.
# Bing Translator is no longer supported as the public API requires authentication.

